          "[Couse module viewed, Course Module Completion, Assignment Form Viewed, Assignment Uploaded, Assignment Updated, Assignment Status Viewed, Discussion Viewed, Discussion Made, Personal Achievement, Group’s achievements viewed, Viewed list of groups, Viewed Group’s Profile]",
          "Data was collected and aggregated continuously. Study also includes separation between control group and a grooup that receives feedback at specific moments in time.",
          "k-Means",
          "-",
          "3",
          "Intense Students: Students who exhibited, by the end of the course, the most activity when it comes to usage time, frequency of visits and completion of learning tasks.\n\nMiddle: Middle activity\n\nLight: generally inactive",
          "It may be recommended to increase cognitively and behaviorally interesting instructions for students with low course engagement levels to move to the intense level.\n\nFeedback mechanism needs improvement since it does not lead to better performance.",
          "Being willing to fully participate in the course was a mandatory requirement to participate in the study.\n\nDifferences between control group and experimental group are measured using ANCOVA tests.\n\nNo differences between groups on academic achievement or affective engagement. ",
          "Small sample size, with selection bias.\n\nEthical considerations between a group that receives feedback while another does not.\n\nUndisclosed criteria for selection of clusters.\n\nSpecific to online contexts. \n\n\n"
